&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You're attempting to use a flow control statement in your query, where you actually need a flow control &lt;em&gt;function&lt;/em&gt;. Use the &lt;code&gt;if()&lt;/code&gt; function instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Try this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;$sql="UPDATE timekeeping SET actualend = timestamp(NOW()), logoutdate = date(NOW()),
totalhours = ((SELECT sum(time_to_sec(timediff(actualend,actualstart))/3600) AS
'totalhours') - 1.50), 
excesstime = if(totalhours &amp;gt; 8,totalhours-8,0)
  WHERE actualend IS NULL and fullname = '$loginuser[fullname]'";
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The flow control statements are used in stored procedures, triggers, etc. and aren't valid in single-line queries.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MySQL reference &lt;a href="http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.5/en/control-flow-functions.html#function_if" rel="nofollow"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

