&lt;p&gt;No, as soon as the first &lt;code&gt;true&lt;/code&gt; is found, it goes straight to the code in the braces. If you used an 'AND' keyword, then it would check the second condition.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You may want to look at operator / logic precedence. For example, what would happen for the following conditions?:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;if($a = $b AND $c = $d AND $e = $f)...
if($a = $b AND $c = $d OR $e = $f)...
if($a = $b OR $c = $d AND $e = $f)...
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://php.net/manual/en/language.operators.precedence.php" rel="nofollow"&gt;http://php.net/manual/en/language.operators.precedence.php&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
